issue.title: Properly handle nested attributes
issue.body:
Example of item (address -> geo):

```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Leanne Graham",
  "username": "Bret",
  "email": "Sincere@april.biz",
  "website": "hildegard.org",
  "address": {
    "street": "Kulas Light",
    "suite": "Apt. 556",
    "city": "Gwenborough",
    "zipcode": "92998-3874",
    "geo": {
      "lat": "-37.3159",
      "lng": "81.1496"
    }
  }
}
```

We should provide better support for: 
- filtering: join values + text
- sorting: probably just skip 
- rendering: print all attributes iterating nestes hashes

issue.title: Remote collections
issue.body:
Allow to pull the collection YAML/JSON from a remote resource:

```yaml
# data/config.yaml

remote_collection: https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users
```

This will also allow to create Tonic collections for example from your remote APIs 🙌🏼

pull_request.body:
The helper `setUrl` is a bit "obscure" 😅... why you would need to change the host without a redirect 🤔? It seems something too "low level" for Ralix. It was more a private function that we decided, at that time, to expose it as public api. After writing more than 10 Ralix apps we've never use it, so I think it's time to ✂️

I take the opportunity to refactor a bit the `setParams` helper and how it works:
- simpler signature: 
`setParam(param, value, { url = currentUrl(), update = false } = {})` => 
`setParam(param, value)`
- always update history via pushState
- if `value` is `null`, remove the param from current url object
- allow to set multiple values at once

**EXTRAS**
- ➕ Implements and closes #76 
- 📝 minor documentation enhancements
- ⬆️ `yarn upgrade`

pull_request.title: 🔧 Refactor getParams/setParams and ✂️ remove setUrl
pull_request.body:
The helper `setUrl` is a bit "obscure" 😅... why you would need to change the host without a redirect 🤔? It seems something too "low level" for Ralix. It was more a private function that we decided, at that time, to expose it as public api. After writing more than 10 Ralix apps we've never use it, so I think it's time to ✂️

I take the opportunity to refactor a bit the `setParams` helper and how it works:
- simpler signature: 
`setParam(param, value, { url = currentUrl(), update = false } = {})` => 
`setParam(param, value)`
- always update history via pushState
- if `value` is `null`, remove the param from current url object
- allow to set multiple values at once

**EXTRAS**
- ➕ Implements and closes #76 
- 📝 minor documentation enhancements
- ⬆️ `yarn upgrade`

pull_request.title: 🔧 Refactor getParams/setParams and ✂️ remove setUrl
pull_request.body:
The helper `setUrl` is a bit "obscure" 😅... why you would need to change the host without a redirect 🤔? It seems something too "low level" for Ralix. It was more a private function that we decided, at that time, to expose it as public api. After writing more than 10 Ralix apps we've never use it, so I think it's time to ✂️

I take the opportunity to refactor a bit the `setParams` helper and how it works:
- simpler signature: 
`setParam(param, value, { url = currentUrl(), update = false } = {})` => 
`setParam(param, value)`
- always update history via pushState
- if `value` is `null`, remove the param from current url object
- allow to set multiple values at once

**EXTRAS**
- ➕ Implements and closes #76 
- 📝 minor documentation enhancements
- ⬆️ `yarn upgrade`
